'''Ethylenedinitramine''' ('''EDNA''')is an [[explosive]] [[chemical compound]] of the [[nitroamine]] class.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1039/TF9484400677| title = The thermal decomposition of explosives. Part I. Ethylenedinitramine and tetryl| journal = Transactions of the Faraday Society| volume = 44| pages = 677| year = 1948| last1 = Robertson| first1 = A. J. B}}</ref>

[[Ednatol]] is a high explosive comprising about 58% ethylenedinitramine and 42% [[TNT]].

