'''''The Oil Gush in Balakhany''''' ({{lang-az|Balaxanıda neft fontanı}}) is a film directed by the pioneer of [[Cinema of Azerbaijan|cinema in Azerbaijan]], [[Alexandre Michon]], it was filmed on August 4, 1898 in [[Balakhany]], [[Baku]] and presented at the [[Exposition Universelle (1900)|International Paris Exhibition]].<ref>[http://azer.com/aiweb/categories/magazine/53_folder/53_articles/53_100years.html Aydin Kazimzade. "Cinema in Azerbaijan: Pre-Soviet Era", ''Azerbaijan International, 5(3)'', Autumn 1997]</ref> The film was shot using a 35mm film on a Lumière [[cinematograph]].
