'''Virtus''' is the name of a new chipset developed by scientists at the [[Nanyang Technological University]] and [[ASTAR Institute for Infocomm Research]]. It allows communication between devices at speeds as high as 1000 times faster than the current [[Bluetooth]] technology.<ref>{{cite news|title=VIRTUS Chipset Is 1000 Times Faster Than Bluetooth|url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/technology/1112542469/virtus-chipset-is-1000-times-faster-than-bluetooth/|accessdate=June 8, 2012|newspaper=RedOrbit|date=May 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=NTU and I2R scientists invent revolutionary chipset for high-speed wireless data transfer|url=http://www.spacedaily.com/reports/NTU_and_I2R_scientists_invent_revolutionary_chipset_for_high_speed_wireless_data_transfer_999.html|accessdate=June 8, 2012|newspaper=Space Daily|date=May 29, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=New chip 1,000 times faster than Bluetooth|url=http://www.tgdaily.com/hardware-features/63632-new-chip-1000-times-faster-than-bluetooth|accessdate=June 8, 2012|newspaper=TG Daily|date=May 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Revolutionary Chipset for High-Speed Wireless Data Transfer|url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2012/05/120524122931.htm|accessdate=June 8, 2012|newspaper=Science Daily|date=May 24, 2012}}</ref> 

